# Architecture

## One-way data flow

```
app/ (screens) → src/hooks/ → src/stores/ + src/services/ → src/lib/supabase.ts
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — Supabase in a screen
const { data } = await supabase.from("messages").select("*");

// ✅ GOOD — hook orchestrates service + store
const { messages, sendMessage } = useMessages(roomId);
```

## Layer rules

| Layer | May call | Must NOT call |
|-------|----------|---------------|
| `app/`, `src/components/` | hooks, UI components | supabase, services directly |
| `src/hooks/` | stores, services | supabase (except realtime in dedicated hooks) |
| `src/stores/` | services | supabase directly (except existing authStore) |
| `src/services/` | supabase | React hooks, components |

## Scope discipline

- Smallest correct diff — no unrelated refactors
- Read surrounding code and match existing patterns
- No premature abstractions or over-engineering
